Nike Dunk Low College Navy Grey (W)
results.story: The women's Nike Dunk Low SP ‘College Navy’ delivers a two-tone colorway of the retro hoops shoe originally released in 1985. The all-leather upper combines a navy blue base with contrasting overlays in Wolf Grey. An unexpected pop of color arrives via Nike branding in University Red on the heel tab and woven tongue tag, while satin laces and a matching collar lining add to the shoe’s luxe look. A translucent rubber outsole offers grippy traction underfoot.

Samarria Brevard x Wmns Numeric 213 'White Blue'
results.story: Designed in collaboration with the Numeric team rider, the Samarria Brevard x New Balance women’s Numeric 213 ‘White Blue’ makes use of a canvas upper with a reinforced suede toe cap and ollie panel. The pristine white finish is contrasted by aqua-colored detailing on the heel tab and woven tongue tag. The former is embellished with a unique dragonfly graphic, the latter with dual NB and Samarria branding. A polyurethane insole provides lightweight cushioning, while a gum rubber outsole delivers grippy traction underfoot.

Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low Premium ‘Medium Curry’ dresses the retro silhouette in a suede upper finished in warm, autumnal hues. A cream-hued base is contrasted by curry brown overlays at the toe and heel, while Fossil coloring is applied to the Swoosh and heel tab, the latter marked with traditional Nike branding. The low-top rides on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring a grippy traction pattern virtually identical to another mid ‘80s hoops shoe, the Air Jordan 1.

Nike Air Max 1 Clot Kiss of Death (2021)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the CLOT x Nike Air Max 1 ‘Kiss of Death’ revives a fan-favorite collaborative colorway initially released in 2006. Like the original, the retro runner is marked by a deconstructed tan suede upper with transparent paneling on the toe box and a scaly texture on the Swoosh. The heel overlay undergoes a color flip, featuring an orange CLOT logo against a red backdrop while the translucent rubber outsole reveals a reflexology-inspired graphic in a new multicolor design.

results.name: CLOT x Air Max 1 PS 'Kiss of Death' 2021
results.story: Built for little kids, the 2021 reissue of the CLOT x Nike Air Max 1 PS ‘Kiss of Death’ brings back a coveted collaboration from 2006 — the first ever joint effort between the Swoosh and Edison Chen’s streetwear brand. Updated with refreshed details, the sneaker’s standout features remain intact, including a transparent toe box, scaly red leather Swoosh and deconstructed ostrich-skin collar. They’re joined by a reflective heel overlay in red leather, along with upgraded reflexology-inspired graphics on the custom sockliner and translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro PS 'Stealth 2.0'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro PS ‘Stealth 2.0’ brings back a 2006 colorway in little kid sizing. The mid-top silhouette features a tumbled white leather upper with semi-translucent netting on the quarter panels and light grey molded eyelets. A royal blue Jumpman adorns a silver reflective tongue, matching the sneaker’s lace locks and collar lining. A second Jumpman icon is embroidered on the back heel. This scaled-down edition features a full-length foam midsole that lacks the visible Air heel unit of the original.

results.name: adidas Continental 80 END German Engineering Cream
results.story: The END. x adidas Continental 80 ‘German Engineering’ takes inspiration from the golden age of motorsport, featuring a premium build that nods to iconic German sports cars. Specifically, the ‘60s and ‘70s color catalogs of BMW and Porsche inform this pair’s aesthetic, featuring a cream-colored leather and suede upper with multicolor three-stripes. Mismatched adidas and END. branding lands on each shoe’s heel tab and tongue, while the lateral heel displays ‘Made in Germany’ text and the sneaker’s numbered edition, which is capped at 500 pairs.

adidas Continental 80 END German Engineering White
results.story: Limited to 500 pairs, the END. x adidas Continental 80 ‘German Engineering’ pays tribute to German technical ingenuity in the field of motorsport. The UK-based retailer dresses the retro silhouette in a white tumbled leather upper, featuring multi-colored three-stripes that nod to iconic race car liveries associated with BMW M Sport and the Martini Racing Porsche. Mismatched adidas and END. branding is applied to each tongue and heel tab, while the lateral heel is stamped with ‘Made in Germany’ and the sneaker’s numbered edition.

Nike Air Max 1 clot Kiss of Death CHA
results.story: The CLOT x Nike Air Max 1 ‘Kiss of Death CHA’ delivers a play on the original collaboration between the Swoosh and Edison Chen’s streetwear brand. While the older shoe was inspired by reflexology, its successor takes its design cues from tea, deemed by CLOT as one of the necessities of Chinese life. The original’s defining attributes remain unchanged, including a clear toe box, deconstructed collar and translucent rubber outsole, the latter marked with a familiar pressure-point graphic. The suede upper is rendered in tan and brown paneling with a red leather Swoosh. The same crimson hue is repeated on CLOT branding embroidered on the heel overlay.

results.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro TD 'Stealth 2.0'
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro TD ‘Stealth 2.0’ celebrates the 15th anniversary of a popular colorway in scaled-down build made for growing feet. Like the original, the upper is constructed from tumbled white leather with Jumpman branding on the heel. A second Jumpman decorates a silver reflective tongue, a hallmark feature of Tinker Hatfield’s 1990 design. It’s joined by additional AJ5 floursihes, including quarter panel netting and shark tooth detailing on the midsole.

Jordan 5 Retro White Stealth (2021)
results.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Stealth 2.0’ delivers a refreshed take on the original ‘Stealth’ Air Jordan 5 from 2006. The mid-top makes use of tumbled white leather throughout the upper, accented with powder blue Jumpman branding on the back heel and reflective silver tongue. A pale grey finish is applied to the midsole, featuring a visible Nike Air unit in the heel and a subtle paint splatter effect on the AJ5’s signature shark tooth detailing.

results.name: Kyle Kuzma x RHUDE x Clyde All-Pro Low
results.story: The Kyle Kuzma x RHUDE x PUMA Clyde All-Pro Low reunites the NBA star with Rhuigi Villaseñor, the founder of LA-based streetwear brand RHUDE. Their low-top sequel to the Clyde All-Pro Kuzma Mid features an engineered Matryx knit upper with durable carbon threads and reinforced overlays in leather and synthetic suede. The sneaker rides on a full-length ProFoam+ midsole, enhanced with a Pebax drop in the heel for added cushioning and responsiveness.

results.name: Nike Air Max 90 NRG Bacon (2021)
results.story: The 2021 reissue of the DQM x Nike Air Max 90 ‘Bacon’ brings back the coveted colorway originally released in 2004 as a collaboration with Dave’s Quality Meat. The shoe’s distinctive palette, featuring an off-white leather base with red suede overlays, a pink leather Swoosh and brown TPU accents, is intended to evoke the look of strips of bacon. The concept reflected the unique butcher shop aesthetic of the legendary NYC sneaker boutique founded in 2003 by Dave Ortiz and Chris Keefe.

Nike Air Max Pre-Day Light Liquid Lime
results.story: Releasing as part of the brand’s 2021 Air Max Day celebration, the Nike Air Max Pre-Day ‘Liquid Lime’ delivers a new addition to the Air Max family, one that carries the torch for previous generations of the vaunted sneaker line. The sneaker’s retro aesthetic is bound up in a sustainable build, comprising a bright green textile upper made from 100% recycled polyester, and a black rubber outsole built with at least 13% Nike Grind Rubber. The shoe’s standout feature is the visible Air sole unit in the heel, unchanged from the one used in the Air Max 1 and 90, but fully exposed and not viewed through an enclosed window.

results.name: Reebok Question Mid Candyland
results.story: Launching as part of a retro collection inspired by the classic Hasbro board game, the Reebok Question Mid ‘Candy Land’ dresses Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe in unique textures and colorful prints. The mid-top makes use of a white leather upper with a polka-dot toe cap and prismatic quarter panels that point the way to the Rainbow Trail. Soft quilted detailing is applied to the collar, while grassy green textile covers the tongue. The latter is marked with Candy Land branding in pink lettering, matching the embroidered Question logo on the heel tab.

InstaPump Fury OG 'Ombre Pack - Alert Yellow'
results.story: Launching as part of the ‘Ombre Pack,’ the Reebok InstaPump Fury OG ‘Alert Yellow’ outfits Steve Smith’s creation in a grey mesh upper with matching pull tabs at the tongue and heel. The sneaker’s inflatable cage is activated with a white rubber Pump button and finished in a gradient blend of pink and yellow. The same hues are applied to stylized Vector branding on the heel panel. A decoupled EVA midsole with Reebok Hexalite provides lightweight cushioning.
